column2: Sunny- moderately rough-but no white caps.
Partly cloudy- first time we've been on lake this year- water 52 degrees.
Sunny hot clear.  Ducks and loons.
Sunny and warm.  Water very low.
Unseasonably warm weather. lake level higher than last year.
Hot- humid. saw loons + 2 eagles. rained hard last night.
Wavy. partly cloudy. gulls- eagles- ducks + loon on lake.
Sunny- rain early this am- hot + humid.
Sunny and gulls and loons on lake.  First reading when Powell marsh sludge not entering lake.
Sunny- calm- rain last night- beautiful day- and six boats on the lake.
3" of rain past two days.  Light waves.
Mostly sunny- loons and gulls on lake- and water is very calm.
Sunny- light breeze- and rain last night.
Sunny- slight breeze- and weather is in the 60's.
First secchi reading of the year.  Partly cloudy.
Hazy- calm- and algae bloom on the surface.
Sunny- windy and the temperature is 88 degrees F.  Four deer and two loons.
Hot- humid- calm- and four fishing boats on the lake.
Sunny and light wind.  Loons and hawks.
Sunny- very bright and light wind.  Beaver Dam between marsh culvert and lake- water is much clearer.
Sunny- calm- and the weather is in the 60s.  Beautiful fall day.
Light wind- rain yesterday- eagle and loon on lake.
Sunny- very warm- no wind- perfect day.
Two loons on lake- sunny- and warm.
Light wind- rain and high winds yesterday- and loons.
Light wind- sunny- and 1 1/2" rain yesterday.
First sunny day after a week of a lot of rain.
Sunny- light wind.  Tree pollen on surface.
Sunny- warm.  Lake level going down.  Iron floc on shoreline.
Light wind.  Beautiful day.  More weeds visible just below surface.
Partly sunny- hot.  Lake level lower.  Iron floc on shoreline.  Light wind.
Loons- seagulls on lake.  Iron floc on shoreline
Light wind- partly sunny. Iron floc on shoreline.
Sunny- windy.  First day in 2 weeks of both sun and light winds.
sunny- windy- first day with sun in over a week and a half     sunny and windy. First day of sun in more than a week and a half.
sunny- hazy- pine pollen on surface- first day in three weeks of both sun and calm- water
light wind- sunny- some iron floc on sand bottom- very little water coming in from marsh
sunny- no water coming in from marsh
lake very calm- no water coming in from dikes- (valve shut off)
best reading ever- no water coming in from dikes- water visibly clearer
hazy sun- light chop- no water coming in from dikes
Sunny- warm.  First sunny day in several days.  Iron floc in bay.
Sunny- warm.  No rain for several days.  No water coming in from marsh.
3 loons- sunny and warm.  No water coming in from the marsh.
Sunny- no clouds.  Light wind.  Weather in 70s after several 90s days.
Beautiful- sunny- warm day.  Sampled with Sandy Wickman of DNR as she showed us collection techniques.
Drain hose missing from water sampler; Sunny- light wind.  First sample after our 6+" of rain 5 days ago.
First time on the lake this year.  Moderate wind- sunny.
Perfect day to sample.  No iron floc coming in from Powell Marsh.
Light chop.  No water coming in from marsh.
Slightly overcast.  No water coming in from Powell Marsh.
Sunny.  Water very clear.  No water coming in from Powell Marsh.
Sunny.  Checking Secchi at the request of Jim Kreitlow of DNR.
Checking Secchi at the request of Jim Kreitlow of DNR.
Sunny.  1" of rain 2 days ago.  No water coming in from Powell Marsh.
Sunny. No wind.  No water coming in from Powell Marsh.
Sunny- cool.  Small amount of water coming in from Powell Marsh ditches.
First day in June that is both sunny and calm.  No water from Powell Marsh.  No rain lately.
Sunny.  Calm.  Powell Marsh ditches loaded with iron floc.
Sunny- light wind.  2 loons on lake.
Sunny- calm.  Little rain all summer (less than 1/2 ").  No water coming in from Powell Marsh.
Hot.  Still no rain and no water from Powell Marsh.
Breezy- sunny.  No water from Powell Marsh.
Our best Secchi reading so far.  No water coming in from Powell Marsh.
Sunny- calm.  Still no water from Powell Marsh.
Sunny.  Light wind.  2" of rain 2 days ago.  Small amount of water coming in from Powell Marsh.
Sunny- no wind at all- perfect for testing.  Best reading ever.
Sunny- 5 swans- loon- gulls and ducks on lake.
Sunny.  East wind.  1" rain 2 days ago.
Light wind.  Sunny. Light wind.  Sunny.
Partly sunny- first calm day all week.
Lots of rain- sunny- calm.  Perfect day for testing.  1 adult and 1 juvenile loon on lake
Clarity less than earlier in the summer.  Lots of floc on sad on shoreline.
Sunny- light wind today. Huge winds yesterday.

column1: Pine pollen on surface of water.
2 loons on lake Sunny- very hot- calm.
Temperature in 60's. Partly cloudy- light breeze.

column2: Sunny- very light breeze- iron floc on shoreline sand
Sunny- light breeze- 1/2" of rain yesterday.  Very little water coming in from Powell Marsh.
Sunny- breezy- upper 60's.  Very little water coming in from Powell Marsh.
Water is low- but not as low as 2012.  partly sunny warm.
Light breeze- 1 loon- water coming into lake from Powell Marsh.
Lake is very dark.  Sunny- cool
Sunny- light breeze- 2 loons.  Very little rain lately.  Very little- if any- water coming in from Powell Marsh.
Sunny- breezy. Rainy and windy yesterday.  Lake level low
Partly sunny- breezy.  Water very brown.
Sunny. Eagles overhead. Abundance of weeds visible.
Sunny. Calm- perfect day.  1 loon on lake
Cool last night. 2 loons on lake. Sunny with light breeze.
Sunny- breezy- lake still cloudy and dark.  Iron floc on shore sand
Sunny. Calm. 1 loon on lake.  Lake very dark with lots of iron floc on shoreline.
Mostly sunny. Calm.  Lake still dark and shoreline still full of iron floc.
Sunny- light wind- 2 swans and 1 loon.
Hazy sun- light breeze.  Goose family and loon on lake
Sunny- calm- 2 swans- 3 loons and 2 blue herons
Sunny- light breeze.  One loon on lake
First monitoring for this year.  Breezy- partly sunny.
Hazy sun- very calm- 2 loons on lake.
